Overview

Here I present a preliminary exploration of data from pinto abalone that were tagged and tracked at Pt. Loma between 2015-11-13 and 2016-05-17. The goal is to evaluate how to best filter the results to minimize positional errors and maximize information about movement distances, aggregation, etc.

For starters, filtered data consisted of a subset of abalone and sync tag data that had a horizontal position error (HPE) of \(\leq\) 50, a speed between detections of \(\leq\) 0.2 m/s, a computed distance between detections of \(\leq\) 20 m. This reduced the number of detections from 23116 to 21788 for abalone tags (5.7% of detections removed), and 146603 to 133071 for sync tags (9.2% of detections removed).

Abalone tag movement speed between detections

The vast majority of abalone speeds appears to be less than 0.2 m/s, which could serve as a first pass cut-off for filtering.
